f=Engineering/aegis/custom/secure-code-review/assets/stack-notes-laravel-security-2026-07.md · h1:Stack Notes Laravel Security (dated 2026-07)=**Applies business's stack-profile names Laravel/PHP.** Method authority: `secure-code-review` `threat-model` (stack-agnostic classes there; note maps them Laravel mechanics). Source: affaan-m/everything-claude-code `laravel-security`, adopted 2026-07-10, condensed. Verify against current Laravel docs months old. · h2:Review checklist by layer=**Core settings:** `APP_DEBUG=false` prod `APP_KEY` set, rotated compromise `SESSION_SECURE_COOKIE=true`, `SESSION_HTTP_ONLY=true`, `SAME_SITE=lax` (strict sensitive flows) trusted proxies configured HTTPS detection sessions regenerated login/privilege change. **AuthN:** Sanctum/Passport API auth (`auth:sanctum` middleware) short-lived tokens refresh sensitive data tokens revoked logout/compromise passwords `Hash::make()` only, `Password::min(12)->letters()->mixedCase()->numbers()->symbols()` rule password broker resets. **AuthZ:** policies model-level checks (`$this->authorize('update', $project)`) route-level `can:update,project` middleware never derive authorization request payloads. **Input:** Form Requests validation (authorize() rules()) strict types never trust payloads derived fields. **Mass assignment:** `$fillable`/`$guarded` always; `Model::unguard()` finding prefer DTOs/explicit mapping. **Injection/XSS/CSRF:** Eloquent/query-builder parameter binding, raw SQL flag Blade `{{ }}` default; `{!! !!}` sanitized trusted HTML `VerifyCsrfToken` on, `@csrf` forms, `sanctum.stateful` domains configured SPAs. **Files:** validate size MIME extension Form Request (`mimes:pdf\|max:5120`) store non-public disk malware-scan risk warrants. **Rate limiting:** `throttle` auth write endpoints `RateLimiter::for('login')` keyed normalized email, e.g. 5/min stricter login/reset/OTP. **Secrets/data:** secrets VCS env secrets manager rotate exposure invalidate sessions `'encrypted'` casts sensitive columns logs redact email/token/card (`[REDACTED]`), never passwords. **Headers/CORS:** SecurityHeaders middleware CSP, HSTS (subdomains/preload all-HTTPS), `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `nosniff`, `Referrer-Policy` `config/cors.php` explicit origins, **no wildcards authenticated routes**, minimal headers, `supports_credentials` deliberate. **Supply chain:** `composer audit` aegis's vuln-pipeline cadence prompt CVE updates (joint ops maintenance-hygiene). **Signed URLs:** `URL::temporarySignedRoute` `signed` middleware temporary tamper-proof links (downloads, invites). · h2:Ties=Findings route through aegis's vuln-pipeline schema; verified-patching closes them., cypher's attack playbooks include classes Laravel target scope.